9:
...We went down for quite a ways.
Are we in the middle of the ocean?
12:
Well, yeah, but it's not that deep. I
have a feeling our luck's gonna turn
around here!
20:
There's plenty of goodies lurking in
the ruins of intact buildings.
21:
Especially in spaces that lead
further underground.
25:
Back in the desert, a lot of the ruins
had underground sections, right?
29:
Yeah, all that sand makes it easy to
hide things away, or at least that's
what I've heard.
33:
Not everything that's hidden away is
necessarily treasure, though!
35:
Still, wouldn't it be fun to find a
secret passageway to an
underwater city—
39: Hold on, I see something over there!
43: Never a dull day with her around...
54:
Guess luck's on our side today. This
has got to be worth a fortune.
58:
Whoa... Now we'll never have to eat
plain curry with nothing in it again!
69:
This is the weird stone that cursed
me back then! No doubt about it!
73:
Y-you sure it's okay to touch it
again?!
76: Oh. Uh, I dunno? Seems fine at least.
80:
Hmm... My body's still the same
though.
84:
Maybe this stone just looks like the
cursed one? Could be an entirely
different thing.
86:
Maybe. Now that I think about it, the
one I touched was a lot more glowy.
91:
Couldn't hurt to take this one back
with us though.
95:
Yeah! Studying it could give us a
hint—
105:
What's wrong? It's not like it's THAT
big—
121:
This sensation in the air... I think this
place is about to fall apart!
123: That's what happened the last time!
127:
You couldn't have given us a
warning?!
130:
Sorry, it slipped my mind! More
importantly, we gotta get outta here!
144: Then please get us to safety!
152:
Phew... Totally thought we were
goners for a second there.
156:
Flana, you sure it was all right to give
up on the stone?
160:
Psh, do you even need to ask? You
guys are way more important!
Besides, there's no guarantee it was
gonna be helpful anyway.
167:
It's not like we floated out
empty-handed either!
172: Haha, you sure are something else.
177:
Looks like we can treat ourselves to
a fancy dinner tonight!
